{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":433,"text":"I want you to imagine this for a moment."},{"time":3204,"text":"Two men, Rahul and Rajiv,"},{"time":6099,"text":"living in the same neighborhood,"},{"time":7957,"text":"from the same educational background, similar occupation,"},{"time":11252,"text":"and they both turn up at their local accident emergency"},{"time":14020,"text":"complaining of acute chest pain."},{"time":16836,"text":"Rahul is offered a cardiac procedure,"},{"time":19960,"text":"but Rajiv is sent home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22771,"text":"What might explain the difference in the experience"},{"time":25281,"text":"of these two nearly identical men?"},{"time":28533,"text":"Rajiv suffers from a mental illness."},{"time":32020,"text":"The difference in the quality of medical care"},{"time":35119,"text":"received by people with mental illness is one of the reasons"},{"time":37980,"text":"why they live shorter lives"},{"time":39895,"text":"than people without mental illness."},{"time":41478,"text":"Even in the best-resourced countries in the world,"},{"time":44148,"text":"this life expectancy gap is as much as 20 years."},{"time":48918,"text":"In the developing countries of the world, this gap"},{"time":50843,"text":"is even larger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53468,"text":"But of course, mental illnesses can kill in more direct ways"},{"time":56327,"text":"as well. The most obvious example is suicide."},{"time":59688,"text":"It might surprise some of you here, as it did me,"},{"time":62343,"text":"when I discovered that suicide is at the top of the list"},{"time":65280,"text":"of the leading causes of death in young people"},{"time":67845,"text":"in all countries in the world,"},{"time":69493,"text":"including the poorest countries of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72885,"text":"But beyond the impact of a health condition"},{"time":75719,"text":"on life expectancy, we're also concerned"},{"time":78089,"text":"about the quality of life lived."},{"time":80783,"text":"Now, in order for us to examine the overall impact"},{"time":83032,"text":"of a health condition both on life expectancy"},{"time":85405,"text":"as well as on the quality of life lived, we need to use"},{"time":88563,"text":"a metric called the DALY,"},{"time":89949,"text":"which stands for a Disability-Adjusted Life Year."},{"time":94236,"text":"Now when we do that, we discover some startling things"},{"time":96757,"text":"about mental illness from a global perspective."},{"time":99579,"text":"We discover that, for example, mental illnesses are"},{"time":102843,"text":"amongst the leading causes of disability around the world."},{"time":107431,"text":"Depression, for example, is the third-leading cause"},{"time":110166,"text":"of disability, alongside conditions such as"},{"time":113138,"text":"diarrhea and pneumonia in children."},{"time":116490,"text":"When you put all the mental illnesses together,"},{"time":118594,"text":"they account for roughly 15 percent"},{"time":120856,"text":"of the total global burden of disease."},{"time":124062,"text":"Indeed, mental illnesses are also very damaging"},{"time":128573,"text":"to people's lives, but beyond just the burden of disease,"},{"time":134018,"text":"let us consider the absolute numbers."},{"time":136730,"text":"The World Health Organization estimates"},{"time":138789,"text":"that there are nearly four to five hundred million people"},{"time":141894,"text":"living on our tiny planet"},{"time":144077,"text":"who are affected by a mental illness."},{"time":145738,"text":"Now some of you here"},{"time":147457,"text":"look a bit astonished by that number,"},{"time":150055,"text":"but consider for a moment the incredible diversity"},{"time":152548,"text":"of mental illnesses, from autism and intellectual disability"},{"time":155702,"text":"in childhood, through to depression and anxiety,"},{"time":158383,"text":"substance misuse and psychosis in adulthood,"},{"time":160664,"text":"all the way through to dementia in old age,"},{"time":162300,"text":"and I'm pretty sure that each and every one us"},{"time":165254,"text":"present here today can think of at least one person,"},{"time":168606,"text":"at least one person, who's affected by mental illness"},{"time":171928,"text":"in our most intimate social networks."},{"time":176359,"text":"I see some nodding heads there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179564,"text":"But beyond the staggering numbers,"},{"time":182534,"text":"what's truly important from a global health point of view,"},{"time":185543,"text":"what's truly worrying from a global health point of view,"},{"time":188088,"text":"is that the vast majority of these affected individuals"},{"time":191256,"text":"do not receive the care"},{"time":193265,"text":"that we know can transform their lives, and remember,"},{"time":195731,"text":"we do have robust evidence that a range of interventions,"},{"time":198792,"text":"medicines, psychological interventions,"},{"time":201244,"text":"and social interventions, can make a vast difference."},{"time":204732,"text":"And yet, even in the best-resourced countries,"},{"time":206983,"text":"for example here in Europe, roughly 50 percent"},{"time":209918,"text":"of affected people don't receive these interventions."},{"time":213035,"text":"In the sorts of countries I work in,"},{"time":215352,"text":"that so-called treatment gap"},{"time":217502,"text":"approaches an astonishing 90 percent."},{"time":222389,"text":"It isn't surprising, then, that if you should speak"},{"time":225601,"text":"to anyone affected by a mental illness,"},{"time":228032,"text":"the chances are that you will hear stories"},{"time":230844,"text":"of hidden suffering, shame and discrimination"},{"time":234894,"text":"in nearly every sector of their lives."},{"time":237843,"text":"But perhaps most heartbreaking of all"},{"time":240553,"text":"are the stories of the abuse"},{"time":243242,"text":"of even the most basic human rights,"},{"time":245774,"text":"such as the young woman shown in this image here"},{"time":248631,"text":"that are played out every day,"},{"time":250695,"text":"sadly, even in the very institutions that were built to care"},{"time":254639,"text":"for people with mental illnesses, the mental hospitals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258474,"text":"It's this injustice that has really driven my mission"},{"time":261502,"text":"to try to do a little bit to transform the lives"},{"time":263894,"text":"of people affected by mental illness, and a particularly"},{"time":266640,"text":"critical action that I focused on is to bridge the gulf"},{"time":270489,"text":"between the knowledge we have that can transform lives,"},{"time":273275,"text":"the knowledge of effective treatments, and how we actually"},{"time":275717,"text":"use that knowledge in the everyday world."},{"time":279139,"text":"And an especially important challenge that I've had to face"},{"time":282298,"text":"is the great shortage of mental health professionals,"},{"time":285223,"text":"such as psychiatrists and psychologists,"},{"time":286895,"text":"particularly in the developing world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289683,"text":"Now I trained in medicine in India, and after that"},{"time":292368,"text":"I chose psychiatry as my specialty, much to the dismay"},{"time":295787,"text":"of my mother and all my family members who"},{"time":298015,"text":"kind of thought neurosurgery would be"},{"time":299718,"text":"a more respectable option for their brilliant son."},{"time":302887,"text":"Any case, I went on, I soldiered on with psychiatry,"},{"time":305621,"text":"and found myself training in Britain in some of"},{"time":307916,"text":"the best hospitals in this country. I was very privileged."},{"time":310291,"text":"I worked in a team of incredibly talented, compassionate,"},{"time":313834,"text":"but most importantly, highly trained, specialized"},{"time":317085,"text":"mental health professionals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319276,"text":"Soon after my training, I found myself working"},{"time":321248,"text":"first in Zimbabwe and then in India, and I was confronted"},{"time":323691,"text":"by an altogether new reality."},{"time":326551,"text":"This was a reality of a world in which there were almost no"},{"time":329897,"text":"mental health professionals at all."},{"time":332262,"text":"In Zimbabwe, for example, there were just about"},{"time":334296,"text":"a dozen psychiatrists, most of whom lived and worked"},{"time":337356,"text":"in Harare city, leaving only a couple"},{"time":339482,"text":"to address the mental health care needs"},{"time":341875,"text":"of nine million people living in the countryside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345543,"text":"In India, I found the situation was not a lot better."},{"time":349160,"text":"To give you a perspective, if I had to translate"},{"time":351583,"text":"the proportion of psychiatrists in the population"},{"time":353791,"text":"that one might see in Britain to India,"},{"time":356173,"text":"one might expect roughly 150,000 psychiatrists in India."},{"time":361782,"text":"In reality, take a guess."},{"time":364813,"text":"The actual number is about 3,000,"},{"time":367378,"text":"about two percent of that number."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369842,"text":"It became quickly apparent to me that I couldn't follow"},{"time":372339,"text":"the sorts of mental health care models that I had been trained in,"},{"time":375400,"text":"one that relied heavily on specialized, expensive"},{"time":378339,"text":"mental health professionals to provide mental health care"},{"time":380871,"text":"in countries like India and Zimbabwe."},{"time":383331,"text":"I had to think out of the box about some other model"},{"time":385984,"text":"of care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387607,"text":"It was then that I came across these books,"},{"time":390720,"text":"and in these books I discovered the idea of task shifting"},{"time":393963,"text":"in global health."},{"time":396031,"text":"The idea is actually quite simple. The idea is,"},{"time":398307,"text":"when you're short of specialized health care professionals,"},{"time":401321,"text":"use whoever is available in the community,"},{"time":404370,"text":"train them to provide a range of health care interventions,"},{"time":407307,"text":"and in these books I read inspiring examples,"},{"time":410175,"text":"for example of how ordinary people had been trained"},{"time":413111,"text":"to deliver babies,"},{"time":414464,"text":"diagnose and treat early pneumonia, to great effect."},{"time":418095,"text":"And it struck me that if you could train ordinary people"},{"time":420846,"text":"to deliver such complex health care interventions,"},{"time":423070,"text":"then perhaps they could also do the same"},{"time":425143,"text":"with mental health care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427135,"text":"Well today, I'm very pleased to report to you"},{"time":430004,"text":"that there have been many experiments in task shifting"},{"time":433116,"text":"in mental health care across the developing world"},{"time":435887,"text":"over the past decade, and I want to share with you"},{"time":437950,"text":"the findings of three particular such experiments,"},{"time":440647,"text":"all three of which focused on depression,"},{"time":442734,"text":"the most common of all mental illnesses."},{"time":445169,"text":"In rural Uganda, Paul Bolton and his colleagues,"},{"time":448511,"text":"using villagers, demonstrated that they could deliver"},{"time":452355,"text":"interpersonal psychotherapy for depression"},{"time":454710,"text":"and, using a randomized control design,"},{"time":457382,"text":"showed that 90 percent of the people receiving"},{"time":459627,"text":"this intervention recovered as compared"},{"time":461587,"text":"to roughly 40 percent in the comparison villages."},{"time":465128,"text":"Similarly, using a randomized control trial in rural Pakistan,"},{"time":469268,"text":"Atif Rahman and his colleagues showed"},{"time":471608,"text":"that lady health visitors, who are community maternal"},{"time":474343,"text":"health workers in Pakistan's health care system,"},{"time":477132,"text":"could deliver cognitive behavior therapy for mothers"},{"time":479349,"text":"who were depressed, again showing dramatic differences"},{"time":481857,"text":"in the recovery rates. Roughly 75 percent of mothers"},{"time":484704,"text":"recovered as compared to about 45 percent"},{"time":487269,"text":"in the comparison villages."},{"time":489553,"text":"And in my own trial in Goa, in India, we again showed"},{"time":492639,"text":"that lay counselors drawn from local communities"},{"time":495167,"text":"could be trained to deliver psychosocial interventions"},{"time":497851,"text":"for depression, anxiety, leading to 70 percent"},{"time":500433,"text":"recovery rates as compared to 50 percent"},{"time":502516,"text":"in the comparison primary health centers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505722,"text":"Now, if I had to draw together all these different"},{"time":507691,"text":"experiments in task shifting, and there have of course"},{"time":510223,"text":"been many other examples, and try and identify"},{"time":512597,"text":"what are the key lessons we can learn that makes"},{"time":514615,"text":"for a successful task shifting operation,"},{"time":517693,"text":"I have coined this particular acronym, SUNDAR."},{"time":521549,"text":"What SUNDAR stands for, in Hindi, is \"attractive.\""},{"time":525783,"text":"It seems to me that there are five key lessons"},{"time":527998,"text":"that I've shown on this slide that are critically important"},{"time":530597,"text":"for effective task shifting."},{"time":532780,"text":"The first is that we need to simplify the message"},{"time":535806,"text":"that we're using, stripping away all the jargon"},{"time":538190,"text":"that medicine has invented around itself."},{"time":541511,"text":"We need to unpack complex health care interventions"},{"time":544468,"text":"into smaller components that can be more easily"},{"time":546696,"text":"transferred to less-trained individuals."},{"time":549351,"text":"We need to deliver health care, not in large institutions,"},{"time":551918,"text":"but close to people's homes, and we need to deliver"},{"time":554144,"text":"health care using whoever is available and affordable"},{"time":556916,"text":"in our local communities."},{"time":559297,"text":"And importantly, we need to reallocate the few specialists"},{"time":562177,"text":"who are available to perform roles"},{"time":564245,"text":"such as capacity-building and supervision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567723,"text":"Now for me, task shifting is an idea"},{"time":570055,"text":"with truly global significance,"},{"time":573014,"text":"because even though it has arisen out of the"},{"time":575547,"text":"situation of the lack of resources that you find"},{"time":579045,"text":"in developing countries, I think it has a lot of significance"},{"time":582004,"text":"for better-resourced countries as well. Why is that?"},{"time":584885,"text":"Well, in part, because health care in the developed world,"},{"time":588405,"text":"the health care costs in the [developed] world,"},{"time":590880,"text":"are rapidly spiraling out of control, and a huge chunk"},{"time":593457,"text":"of those costs are human resource costs."},{"time":596877,"text":"But equally important is because health care has become"},{"time":599363,"text":"so incredibly professionalized that it's become very remote"},{"time":603200,"text":"and removed from local communities."},{"time":605955,"text":"For me, what's truly sundar about the idea of task shifting,"},{"time":609677,"text":"though, isn't that it simply makes health care"},{"time":611323,"text":"more accessible and affordable but that"},{"time":614481,"text":"it is also fundamentally empowering."},{"time":617037,"text":"It empowers ordinary people to be more effective"},{"time":620669,"text":"in caring for the health of others in their community,"},{"time":623492,"text":"and in doing so, to become better guardians"},{"time":624981,"text":"of their own health. Indeed, for me, task shifting"},{"time":628263,"text":"is the ultimate example of the democratization"},{"time":630950,"text":"of medical knowledge, and therefore, medical power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636199,"text":"Just over 30 years ago, the nations of the world assembled"},{"time":639650,"text":"at Alma-Ata and made this iconic declaration."},{"time":642623,"text":"Well, I think all of you can guess"},{"time":644228,"text":"that 12 years on, we're still nowhere near that goal."},{"time":647943,"text":"Still, today, armed with that knowledge"},{"time":650608,"text":"that ordinary people in the community"},{"time":653264,"text":"can be trained and, with sufficient supervision and support,"},{"time":656427,"text":"can deliver a range of health care interventions effectively,"},{"time":659699,"text":"perhaps that promise is within reach now."},{"time":663580,"text":"Indeed, to implement the slogan of Health for All,"},{"time":667224,"text":"we will need to involve all"},{"time":669010,"text":"in that particular journey,"},{"time":670669,"text":"and in the case of mental health, in particular we would"},{"time":673615,"text":"need to involve people who are affected by mental illness"},{"time":676518,"text":"and their caregivers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677972,"text":"It is for this reason that, some years ago,"},{"time":680508,"text":"the Movement for Global Mental Health was founded"},{"time":682426,"text":"as a sort of a virtual platform upon which professionals"},{"time":686449,"text":"like myself and people affected by mental illness"},{"time":689256,"text":"could stand together, shoulder-to-shoulder,"},{"time":691968,"text":"and advocate for the rights of people with mental illness"},{"time":694454,"text":"to receive the care that we know can transform their lives,"},{"time":697671,"text":"and to live a life with dignity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700680,"text":"And in closing, when you have a moment of peace or quiet"},{"time":704197,"text":"in these very busy few days or perhaps afterwards,"},{"time":707023,"text":"spare a thought for that person you thought about"},{"time":709777,"text":"who has a mental illness, or persons that you thought about"},{"time":712354,"text":"who have mental illness,"},{"time":713942,"text":"and dare to care for them. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":717746,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}